gomodel:SYNGO_1834  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: hnRNP U binds to the motor protein KIF5A, which makes it a possible adapter protein in axo-dendritic transport (Fig. 1)\nshRNA KD of hnRNP U (Fig.8) negatively affects Kinesin5-dependent dendritic transport of mRNA granules that contain transcripts for synapse marker proteins such as CAMKII (Fig.1/5/8) and Arc (Fig.1).. Experimental description: none given" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2094-7491" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9848-0262" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1190-4481" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4419-210X" ;
